{
  "texts": [
    "Table 1 Search query 1 3 However, it is worth mentioning that we should not compare subject fields using CiteScore.",
    "This metric is not field-normalized, and thus, the different publication and citation behaviour of researchers in different fields affects the values, as well as differences in performance (Elsevier 2024a).",
    "H-indices indicate a balance between the productivity (scholarly output) and citation count of an entity's publications.",
    "For illustration, when h-index of an entity is 9, this implies that the top 9 most-cited publications of the researcher have each received at least 9 citations.",
    "Whilst citation impact is the total number of citations received divided by the total number of publications."
  ]
}